lyrics:
[Verse]
In the Lone Star State, there's a girl named Anna
With sparkling eyes, she swings her tennis racquet
Her love for the game, oh, it truly matters
On the court she shines, like a shooting star cadet

[Chorus]
Anna, Anna, you're the queen of the court
With every swing, your spirit takes flight
Anna, Anna, your loyalty won't distort
For you, Aaron, your heart's beacon of light
